    "The author argues that while AI techniques can significantly enhance cybersecurity measures by enabling automated and robust threat detection, they can also potentiate cybercriminal activities by providing advanced means for complex attacks.",
    "The study highlights the need for companies to balance their cybersecurity frameworks with the emerging risks, especially as ML becomes increasingly integral to both offense and defence in cybersecurity.",
    "There is, however, a notable gap in Mathew's [92] study to understand the motivations behind AI-driven cyberattacks and their broader societal impact.Fazelnia et al. [64] focused on the vulnerabilities in software systems that incorporate AI and ML.",
    "Recognising the growing appeal of these technologies to malicious actors, the paper proposed a framework for characterising attacks and weaknesses specific to AI-enabled systems.",
    "The framework also outlines mitigation techniques and defence strategies, aiming to guide software designers in developing resilient AI-enabled applications."
